  "description": [
    "LETTERS 10 THE EDITOR Cargills Have Big Spread In Conrad Dear Harry I was interested in the article re garding taxes paid by the Farmers Supply Coop of Conrad I believe more articles should be printed which are concrete proof that coops do pay Taxes This article shows that the Farmers Supply of Conrad paid real and per sonal taxes in the amount of 438808 and that Cargills Inc paid 5103 It might be interesting to you to know something about the facilities of Car gills Inc In Conrad they have an ele vator plus an annex which is large enough I believe to set all the Farmers Supply building in and still have room to spare Im not sure of the capacity of their elevator and warehouse in Conrad but would estimate that there must be a capacity of 200000 bushels Then in addition to this they have a vegetable oil plant that must have cost plenty Then further they have an elevator and annex in Ledger that will per haps hold a 100000 bushels and that isnt all they have an elevator and annex in Valler with a capacity in ex cess of 100000 plus a large feed"
  ],
